cast.text:
i think sport betting is tremendously useful in framing the greater crypto perception problem

nearly all normies have no qualms with sports gambling & in fact many routinely engage

the majority of those who participate, lose money, consistently, but still, have no issues with sports betting

now you ask those same people what they think about crypto & you‚Äôre almost guaranteed ‚Äústupid‚Äù or ‚Äúscam‚Äù

we, inside the space, know that our risk/reward is much better than sport betting & yet those who wager sports, call us the scam

this is what we‚Äôve done to ourselves; even the risk-on degenerates think we‚Äôre trash 

extrapolate this to any risk-adverse cohort & now you see the problem‚Äîone that‚Äôs so widely spread & deeply rooted that it‚Äôs virtually impossible to solve at face value 

this is all without consideration of currency risk, custodial risk, hacks & rug risk, etc. 

so the normie that was most likely to convert, now calls us a scam, ie. they won‚Äôt come back, not even to wager on sports
